&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0in 0in 8pt; line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: georgia, palatino;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced Practice Provider (Nurse Practitioner or Physician Assistant)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0in 0in 8pt; line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: georgia, palatino;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;&quot;&gt;Location: North Denver, CO (Thornton, Longmont, Ft. Collins)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style=&quot;margin: 0in 0in 8pt; line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: georgia, palatino;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0in 0in 8pt; line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: georgia, palatino, serif;&quot;&gt;We are seeking a Nurse Practitioner or Physician Assistant experienced in diagnosing, treating, and managing patients with vascular disease, including lower extremity venous insufficiency and peripheral arterial disease.&amp;nbsp; This position is office-based and primarily focused on consultations, ongoing evaluations, and follow-up care. The Advanced Practice Provider will work closely with the physician and perform consultations within his/her scope of practice once trained and qualified.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0in 0in 8pt; line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: georgia, palatino;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
